s together the contributors’ diverse perspectives by noting common themes, similarities, and differences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh1 aApel, Karl-Otto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aApplebaum, Anne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBrandom, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarries, Karsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeidt, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Jane Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNussbaum, Martha C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRagland, C. P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStroud, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWood, Allen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030008755040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300147933423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300147933/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY